race.description: Girls Day Out On Sale Now Handicap (Bm65)
race.comment: Competitive. Waller-trained LIBERTY PARK (4) was last seen 15 days ago in stronger at Randwick-Kensington, where she disappointed with JMac up (vet cleared). He has finished close up at Canterbury his two prior and they read well for this. Maps for a soft run and KWT is booked. The premier Gollan yard starts LIVALITTLE (2), who is bringing two heavily bet wins with the latest at the Sunshine Coast at 70 level. The 3kg claim brings her right into it. MR O'REILLY (5) is busting to win and drops back a touch in trip off the 1L defeat here in a 78. Deserves another chance. CIGAR MAN (10) will use the low barrier and has the blinkers applied for the first time. Brings threatening form to peak.
